“Curse” is also set in a cyber-goth world where the main character is about to meet her end, but is then presented with two buttons “curse” or “fate”. She chooses Fate, thinking it was the right option, but turns out it wasn’t. This is like, you make a decision in life, and bad things just keep happening, and you wonder, did I choose right? I do this for every song btw :)

“Color Chaos” is about a painter who loves their creations, but then starts to hate them. The paintings come to life like a kaleidoscopic nightmare and haunt the painter. This is about any creator,  who has great days and horrible. Bad days give you experience, good days give you happiness. the worst days give lessons, the best days give you memories - a day is never wasted, always remember that :)

MY FIRST VINYL!! This is so special to me that each and every one of you are here with me on this journey :) I love you all so so much, and I plan on making music til i’m EXACTLY 88 years old. When I started Unlike Pluto I never expected any of this, and MANY people around advised me to do something else. But i’m so glad I persevered through with this community, we in this together. I had ups and downs with my music career, kept comparing myself to other artists, went through a few moments of intense depression and anxiety - the only thing that got me through? You, and this music. I love you all so much from the bottom of my heart and soul. With dark music, we spread love :) 

Thank you :)

In 2018 i was completely  lost in my career, so I started making weekly songs called Pluto tapes, and it was the BEST decision I ever made. Every day I would wake up, make a coffee, and work til 10pm. Then I would play games til I slept, RDR2 got me through it :) we are moving on to better things now, but sometimes you gotta appreciate your origin story. Love you all :)

I spent 2 years making a manga / webtoon called Dada Immortal with two of my best friends :) music, movies, tv, anime, are all things that I would lose myself in forgetting about any depression or anxiety I have. during covid, anime literally saved me. I made it my goal to start telling my own weird stories and share with the world, so other people can lose themselves in them too! This is just the beginning, MANY stories to tell. So it would mean the world to me if you read :) 2 chapters out now and new ones released on Wednesdays. Oh and, music out with the chapter too, link in bio :) LOVE YOUUUUUUUU #manga #webtoon
